data.text:
WEES is a non-commercial, educational, FM radio station at 107.9 Mhz on your FM dial, with a public studio in the Gold Coast Mall on the Coastal Highway in Ocean City, Maryland. Reaching a population of over 300,000 in the summer, WEES is the first and only low power FM station in Ocean City. WEES programs are also streamed over over the internet. WEES relies upon community participation in many forms. Volunteer announcers develop their own programs, that are produced live at our Ocean City studio in the Gold Coast Mall. Our Community Calendar alerts listners to upcoming, local activities that may be of interest, it is compiled through station consultation with area business leaders. This information is broadcast live and is also found on the station's Facebook page@WEES RADIO, which contains postings from listners and volunteers. WEES airs early childhood educational programming every weekday morning. At other times, the station airs a variety programs which are consistent with family oriented content. We welcome volunteers that want to start their own weekly shows.

WEES Volunteers: Orginal Live Programming Mondays 7-9 p.m. Wheel of Musical Mayhem and The Progressive Lens Rob Buck, "Radio Rob", hour #1, "The WONDERFUL WHEEL OF MUSICAL MAYHEM" when a random spin of the wheel decides the musical mix. In Hour #2, It's "THE PROGRESSIVE LENS" featuring pioneers, and current purveyors of the Prog Rock genre. Tuesdays. 4-7 p.m. The Tracks of my Years Bob Murphy, "The Captain", hosts "THE TRACKS OF MY YEARS" celebrating birthdays of musical artists, playing #1 hits and his favorite tracks. Tuesdays 8-10 p.m. Rock and Roll Ramble Bob Wigo hosts "THE TUESDAY EVENING ROCK & ROLL RAMBLE" , WITH Classic Rock, Soul, Blues & Americana... Minimum talk and MAXIMUM MUSIC. Wednesdays 6-8 p.m. The After School Detention Show Denis Jenkins, "The Professor" , hosts "BUBBA'S Music Party " with lots of Rock, Blues, and Americana, along with listener requests. Thursdays 5-6 p.m. Craig Johnson, hosts "THE VINYL CURTAIN", an eclectic mix of great tracks from our in-studio turntable. Thursdays 7-10 p.m. The Haze Bill Freedman, hosts "THE HAZE" a musical blend of ground-breaking artists of the 60s, into the 80s, with an emphasis on rare, live, and studio selections not heard anywhere else on radio. Fridays 3-4:30 p.m. Doo-Wop with "the Dean" Dino Fradelos airs the best street corner recordings, a weekly musical trivia contest, and more hits of the 50s and 60s. Saturdays. 10 a.m. - 1 p.m. The Rock and Roll Time Machine Rick Bohs, "The Doctor" , hosts "THE ROCK N SOUL TIME MACHINE", featuring 50's Roots of Rock, 60's Juke Box Memories including THE MOTOWN 6-PACK, album cuts, and tracks from a weekly spotlight-classic vinyl album or CD. Sundays 7-9 p.m. Bourbon Hour & Alt Rock Chaser Joe Youngblood, YankeeJoe, hosts "The Bourbon Hour, Blues with a Burn" to wind down the week. Hour #2 is the "Alt Rock Chaser" focusing on alternative rock to start your week.
